<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880414-0016 </DOCNO><HL> Meditrust Sells 5 Million Shares </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MT </CO><IN> STK </IN><DATELINE> WELLESLEY, Mass.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Meditrust, a health-care real estate investment trust, said it sold five million beneficial-interest shares at $19.25 each. Proceeds will be used to acquire additional health-care facilities.    Meditrust closed in composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange yesterday at $19 a share, unchanged.    The company had about 10.7 million beneficial-interest shares outstanding prior to the offering.    The underwriting was through a syndicate managed by Smith Barney, Harris Upham and Co.; Alex. Brown andamp; Sons Inc.; Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc.; and Robertson Colman andamp; Stephens. </TEXT></DOC>